  "title": "Commis Cook",
  "description": "<p><strong>Why Join Us?</strong><br /></p><p>At Tiong Bahru Bakery, we strongly believe that everyone has value to add to the business and organization.</p><p>We care about your welfare greatly and believe in open and respectful communication between each other, to ensure a <strong>supportive</strong> and <strong>happy work</strong> environment for everyone, a second family who will help you learn and grow into positions of higher responsibilities.</p><p>We are seeking energetic individuals who are great team players. If you have a good attitude, are cheerful and enjoy interacting with people, we are interested in meeting you.<br /></p><p><strong>Job Highlights</strong><br /></p><p>Fun and supportive work environment</p><p>Structured training programme provided</p><p>Career growth opportunity from sustainable and consistent brand expansion</p><p>6- and 12-month new hire incentive, on top of year-end Performance Bonus</p><p>Group-wide staff discounts (F&B and Beauty brands under Spa Esprit Group)</p><p>Medical insurance, fixed OT hours, and leave provisions in line with MOM regulations</p><p>No split shifts<br /></p><p>Responsibilities:<br />• Daily preparation and production of breads and pastries<br />• Handle heavy loading, mixing, packing of ingredients and finished product<br />• Responsible for the consistency and presentation of the products<br />• Pack baked goods for delivery timely<br />• Maintain inventory and storage in an organised manner<br />• Decorate and prepare garnishes for baked goods<br />• Prepare ingredients and food items accordingly to recipes<br />• Assist In conceptualising and creating pastries, desserts and other baked goods<br />• Minimise the wastage and spoilage of ingredients and other food items<br />• Manage and maintain hygiene standards<br /><br />Requirements:<br />• Excellent communication, interpersonal, leadership and organisational skills<br />• Able to cope in a fast-paced environment</p>",
